The paper discusses neuromorphic computing, which is a subfield of computer science that focuses on building computing systems inspired by the brain. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses memristive devices, which are electronic components that can be used to represent synaptic weights in artificial neural networks. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which covers new and innovative technologies. Additionally, the paper discusses phase change memory devices, which are a type of non-volatile memory that can be used as memristive devices. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), which covers the design and implementation of computer hardware. The paper also discusses simulations and experimental results, which suggests that it could belong to cs.EM (Engineering and Control) or cs.SY (Systems and Control), which cover the design and control of complex systems.
